The synthetic RNA probe and primer controls produced typical amplification plots across the range of serial 10-fold dilutions from 10−2 to 10−9 (Table 1
). The shape of the amplification plots obtained for the synthetic probe and primer controls were virtually indistinguishable from those obtained with SARS coronavirus RNA (plots not shown). As indicated in Table 1 residual DNA template was present in the TaqMan control as is evidenced by the positive signal at a dilutions of 10−6 (C
t 37.45) or lower in the no RT control (column 3).
